.TH _printf 3 "April 2026" "Holberton" "_printf manual"

.SH NAME
_printf - simplified printf function

.SH SYNOPSIS
#include "main.h"

int _printf(const char *format, ...);

.SH DESCRIPTION
_printf writes output to stdout according to a format string.

The format string may contain ordinary characters and conversion specifiers.

The following conversion specifiers are supported:
%c - prints a single character
%s - prints a string
%% - prints a percent sign
%d - prints an integer
%i - prints an integer

This function does not handle:
- flags
- field width
- precision
- length modifiers

.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns the number of characters printed (excluding the null byte).
If an error occurs, a negative value is returned.

.SH EXAMPLES
_printf("Hello %s\n", "World");
_printf("Number: %d\n", 10);

.SH SEE ALSO

printf(3)
